The total number of confirmed Covid-19 cases in the North West as of Thursday was 2 965, the provincial Department of Health said on Friday. The province has also recorded 421 recoveries and five deaths. North West's positive cases make up 2.5% of the country's total. It has the fifth most cases in the country, after the Western Cape, Gauteng, Eastern Cape and KwaZulu-Natal. The Rustenburg municipality, which was earlier identified as a hotspot in the province, had so far recorded 1 682 cases and 203 recoveries, department spokesperson Tebogo Lekgethwane said. "Allocation and verification of Covid-19 confirmed cases in the North West province is an ongoing process. The Department of Health will continuously allocate cases after verification to a specific and appropriate location within a particular municipality," said Lekgethwane.  https://www.news24.com/news24/southafrica/news/covid-19-north-west-records-almost-3-000-confirmed-cases-20200626